<div class="jysk-about">
    <div class="container py-5">
        <h1 class="jysk-about-title">Welcome to JYSK!</h1>
        <p class="jysk-about-lead">
            JYSK is an international home furniture company with Scandinavian roots, making it easy to furnish any room in any home and garden.
        </p>

        <section class="jysk-about-section">
            <h2 class="jysk-about-heading">A Man with a Dream!</h2>
            <p>
                It all started with a man who had a dream. Lars Larsen was born in northwestern Denmark and served as an apprentice at a textile manufactory. Later he started his own business: a network of bedding stores. Interestingly, he had almost no money but was full of bright ideas. Soon, the ambitious young entrepreneur found suppliers and a bank willing to help him. Lars Larsen opened the first JYSK store in Aarhus, on the Jutland peninsula, on April 2, 1979.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="jysk-about-section">
            <h2 class="jysk-about-heading">JYSK Today</h2>
            <p>
                Today the JYSK group operates more than 3,500 stores in 50 countries: Denmark, Norway, Sweden, Finland, Poland, Czech Republic, Hungary, Netherlands, Slovakia, Germany, Austria, Switzerland, Iceland, Canada, Greenland, Faroe Islands, Estonia, Latvia, Lithuania, Ukraine, Kosovo, Bulgaria, Kazakhstan, Romania, France, United Kingdom, Slovenia, North Macedonia, Croatia, Italy, Spain, Bosnia and Herzegovina, China, Serbia, Armenia, Montenegro, Indonesia, Greece, Singapore, Albania, Vietnam, Malta, Portugal, Georgia, Tajikistan, Moldova, Belgium, and Kuwait.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="jysk-about-section">
            <h2 class="jysk-about-heading">Our Company</h2>
            <p>
                JYSK is part of the family-owned Lars Larsen Group, with a total turnover of 48.0 billion Danish kroner in the 2023–24 financial year. JYSK's turnover in the same period was 41.4 billion Danish kroner.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="jysk-about-section">
            <h2 class="jysk-about-heading">What Does "JYSK" Mean?</h2>
            <p>
                The word "JYSK" was deliberately chosen for the company name. In Danish, "JYSK" refers to someone or something from the Jutland peninsula — such as Lars Larsen — and is often associated with modesty, conscientiousness, and honesty: the three values Larsen himself embodied. JYSK means trust, and business always remains business.
            </p>
        </section>

